org.jlinalg.polynomial

Class Polynomial<BASE extends IRingElement<BASE>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jlinalg.RingElement<Polynomial<BASE>>
      • org.jlinalg.polynomial.Polynomial<BASE>
  • Type Parameters:
    BASE - The type for the domain of the polynomials' coefficients.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Polynomial<BASE>>, IEuclideanRingElement<Polynomial<BASE>>, IRingElement<Polynomial<BASE>>

    public class Polynomial<BASE extends IRingElement<BASE>>
extends RingElement<Polynomial<BASE>>
implements IEuclideanRingElement<Polynomial<BASE>>
    A class of polynomials. This constructor of class requires that a the factory of a base type is created first and then passed to the constructor. Alternatively, the factory can be used. For example, the following creates a factory for polynomials for a rational domain: 
     PolynomialFactory<Rational>== PolynomialFactory.getFactory(Rational.FACTORY);
    Then, the polynomial "1+2*x^2+2*x^3" can be created as follows: 
     Map<Integer, Rational> coeff1 = new HashMap<Integer, Rational>();
 coeff1.put(0, new Rational(1));
 coeff1.put(1, new Rational(2));
 coeff1.put(2, new Rational(3));
 Polynomial<Rational> polynomial = rationalPolyFactory.get(coeff1);
    Author:
    Andreas Keilhauer, Georg Thimm

    Serialized Form
